claim: Zero compensation from the programs connected to Nuclear weapons and the United States has been made to U.S citizens exposed to nuclear hazards.
premise_source_doc_sentence: By February 2006 over $ 1.2 billion in compensation had been paid to U.S. citizens exposed to nuclear hazards as a result of the U.S. nuclear weapons program , and by 1998 at least $ 759 million had been paid to the Marshall Islanders in compensation for their exposure to U.S. nuclear testing .
